The electrical conduction of undoped PCD can be attributed to the impurities or traps in diamond grains and grain boundaries. After comparing the quality of diamond grown under different CH4/H2, revealed by SEM and Raman analysis, Kulkarni et al. attributed the low resistivity on the order of 10–106 Ω cm to the grain boundaries structure [56, 57]. Lee produced Cu electrode layers, via electroplating, on diamond film surfaces, showing that the main electrical conduction path in undoped PCD films are the grain boundaries within the films [61]. The electrical conduction mechanism, due to impurities [62, 63], had also been investigated by examining the relationship between the material’s temperature and the electrical current through the diamond film. The activation energy can be calculated by using the Eq. (8)8σ=σ0exp-Ea/kT\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
